<p> By my next tour, in 1990, I had my act together much better. I had
the full set of panniers (two front, two rear) and I carefully
selected my gear so that everything fit into them. The only thing I
had on the top of my rack was my mascot, a dinosuar (a plastic
cetiosaurus from the British Museum of Natural History). The bike this
time really was intended for touring: a Panasonic PT3500 with
cantilever brakes, triple chainring, long chainstays, and two
waterbottle mounts. It worked well for me then, hauling me up all the
steep hills in <a href="../oregon.html">Oregon</a>. This time I
brought a sleeping bag with me (a nice down one)

</p>

